3.10	Willie_Davenport	Willie Davenport	William "Willie" D. Davenport (June 8, 1943 â€“ June 17, 2002) was an American athlete, born in Troy, Alabama. William attended Howland High School, a suburb of Warren in Northeast Ohio. He attended college at Southern University and A&amp;M College in Baton Rouge, Louisiana. He participated in hurdling events in four Olympic Games, winning the title in 1968. In 1980, he also took part in the Olympic Winter Games as a runner for the American bobsleigh team.	
